FastBit
1. check out FastBit of version=665
   $ svn checkout https://codeforge.lbl.gov/anonscm/fastbit@665
2. $ ./configure --without-java --enable-xopt --disable-debug
3. $ make -j 3 all
4. $ make --prefix=/xxx/fastbit install

DataSpaces
$ ./configure CC=mpicc FC=mpif90 CXX=mpic++ --with-fastbit=/ccs/home/qsun/fastspace/fb_665/fastbit/trunk/install --enable-fastbit
$  make

Test case: ./tests/fastspace_c
$  qsub job.dspaces.sith.pbs


Issue for dataspaces-fastbit
------------------------------------
1. The number of readers must smaller or equal to the number of servers

2. Put API
   dspaces_put(const char *app_name,
        unsigned int version, int elem_size,
        int xl, int yl, int zl,
        int xu, int yu, int zu,
        void *data)

3. All the data information is put into "metadata.txt" instead of PUT api
   Example:
   	num_attr=3    //number of attributes/variables in one element
   	var1;d        //var_name;var_type
   	var2;f        //use ; to split
   	var3;i

4. Supported datatypes:
	d(DOUBLE), f(FLOAT), i(INT)

5. Value Query API
   dspaces_value_query(const char *app_name,
        unsigned int version, int elem_size,
        void *qcond, void *data)
   The query result is stored in "data", which is pre-allocated by the user
   application. The total data size (Byte) is returned as a return value of 
   dspaces_value_query
 
